1
00:00:02,086 --> 00:00:06,424
I'm Cameron Crowe, the
writer/director of Jerry Maguire.

2
00:00:06,757 --> 00:00:08,801
I'm feeling very
fortunate right now...

3
00:00:08,968 --> 00:00:14,932
...to have Renee, Tom and Cuba
with us to watch Jerry Maguire.

4
00:00:15,099 --> 00:00:18,603
-Awesome.
-A rather momentous reunion.

5
00:00:19,020 --> 00:00:21,939
Thank you for being here, guys.
Let's check it out.

6
00:00:23,983 --> 00:00:26,068
Can we turn the lights down?

7
00:00:27,612 --> 00:00:31,574
How the hell we gonna see
the screen with the lights on?

8
00:00:32,700 --> 00:00:37,288
-That's an excellent idea.
-Oh, this part I like.

9
00:00:41,584 --> 00:00:43,836
The Tom-ster.

10
00:00:44,879 --> 00:00:47,673
This is the world. There are
almost six billion people on it.

11
00:00:50,885 --> 00:00:54,972
I did the voice-over in London
while doing Eyes Wide Shut.

12
00:00:55,139 --> 00:00:57,850
Yes, indeed.
The movie always, for me...

13
00:00:58,017 --> 00:01:00,603
...began with "Magic Bus"
by The Who.

14
00:01:00,811 --> 00:01:05,316
On the day where, Tom, you said,
"Let's make this movie together"...

15
00:01:05,650 --> 00:01:08,027
...we played "Magic Bus"
in my office.

16
00:01:08,194 --> 00:01:13,699
You did the voice-over in the office.
It felt like, "This is the movie."

17
00:01:13,866 --> 00:01:16,869
I remember that.
I went out of my mind.

18
00:01:17,912 --> 00:01:20,748
In Seattle, Dallas Malloy, 16.

19
00:01:21,707 --> 00:01:24,293
Dallas is a real boxer.

20
00:01:26,045 --> 00:01:29,298
-Kicking ass.
-Yeah, you got that right.

21
00:01:31,425 --> 00:01:33,970
Check out what pure joy looks like.

22
00:01:34,345 --> 00:01:39,642
That baseball hit one of the crew on
the head and caused major problems.

23
00:01:39,850 --> 00:01:44,105
-He went straight to the hospital.
-That was that lawsuit, right?

24
00:01:44,313 --> 00:01:45,398
That's funny.

25
00:01:45,731 --> 00:01:47,066
Jerry O'Connell.

26
00:01:47,233 --> 00:01:51,112
-There he is.
-Allan Graf, the stunt coordinator.

27
00:01:51,696 --> 00:01:55,157
Crazy son of a bitch
killed half the stuntmen.

28
00:01:55,366 --> 00:02:00,037
-He tried to kill you.
-He's a good guy, but good Lord!

29
00:02:01,706 --> 00:02:04,125
I'm the guy you don't usually see.

30
00:02:04,750 --> 00:02:08,170
That was a fun day of shooting,
with the owners.

31
00:02:09,046 --> 00:02:10,923
The coaches.

32
00:02:12,341 --> 00:02:14,051
Players.

33
00:02:16,929 --> 00:02:19,056
That was a blast.

34
00:02:19,265 --> 00:02:21,976
Let's talk about the hair
for a moment.

35
00:02:22,184 --> 00:02:24,228
What's up with that hair?

36
00:02:24,437 --> 00:02:28,274
It's rocking. This is
the true sports agent look.

37
00:02:28,441 --> 00:02:29,775
It is.

38
00:02:32,028 --> 00:02:34,322
I'll just write it down.

39
00:02:34,572 --> 00:02:35,614
14 Million x 5

40
00:02:35,865 --> 00:02:39,994
-I can't afford that.
-Winning isn't cheap.

41
00:02:41,662 --> 00:02:44,957
-It's probably a good--
-You're proud, aren't you?

42
00:02:45,916 --> 00:02:49,962
Easy, Renee, your part's coming.
Hang in there, be patient.

43
00:02:55,676 --> 00:02:59,263
-Jay.
-That would be Jann Wenner.

44
00:02:59,472 --> 00:03:02,099
-Publisher of Rolling Stone.
-Really?

45
00:03:02,266 --> 00:03:06,145
-Your first employer.
-Oh, that's classic.

46
00:03:06,312 --> 00:03:09,065
-He returns to--
-He's in Almost Famous too.

47
00:03:09,231 --> 00:03:11,108
Yes, he is.

48
00:03:12,526 --> 00:03:15,529
...in a new commercial
starring you...

49
00:03:15,780 --> 00:03:19,533
...broadcast during a Super Bowl
game you're winning.

50
00:03:19,742 --> 00:03:23,621
-You can't beat that.
-He was just, "Say it faster."

51
00:03:23,788 --> 00:03:26,290
-Take a deep breath.
-That was awesome.

52
00:03:26,457 --> 00:03:28,793
Was the girl 16 or 177

53
00:03:29,001 --> 00:03:31,921
Wanting the big dollar,
things went wrong.

54
00:03:32,171 --> 00:03:37,510
There's no proof of anything.
This guy is a sensational athlete.

55
00:03:38,552 --> 00:03:41,138
Are you Calvin Nack?
Can you sign my card?

56
00:03:41,514 --> 00:03:46,894
You had the flu during this. You had
103 temperature and were puking.

57
00:03:47,561 --> 00:03:52,274
-That scene directed itself.
-Do you remember that day?

58
00:03:52,608 --> 00:03:56,654
It usually works better
when I'm not in the room.

59
00:03:56,862 --> 00:04:00,533
Not true. You still directed.

60
00:04:00,825 --> 00:04:01,867
Hi, baby.

61
00:04:04,161 --> 00:04:08,165
-She does the voice of Babe. Yep.
-Oh, is that true?

62
00:04:10,292 --> 00:04:13,212
This was the first day of filming.
Am I right?

63
00:04:13,587 --> 00:04:15,047
Yeah.

64
00:04:16,006 --> 00:04:18,050
How do you remember that?

65
00:04:18,217 --> 00:04:23,305
Because I was asked down to the set
even though I wasn't filming.

66
00:04:23,806 --> 00:04:25,975
I didn't think that was first.

67
00:04:26,142 --> 00:04:30,604
I think we were rehearsing out
in the hall in between shoots.

68
00:04:31,355 --> 00:04:33,566
My agent. My agent.

69
00:04:34,316 --> 00:04:36,152
No pressure.

70
00:04:38,612 --> 00:04:43,075
Absolutely. The first day.
The first shot is coming right up.

71
00:04:43,325 --> 00:04:47,079
-This is the first thing we filmed.
-Right here?

72
00:04:47,246 --> 00:04:51,750
This is his fourth concussion.
Shouldn't he stop?

73
00:04:51,959 --> 00:04:55,129
It would take a tank
to stop your dad.

74
00:04:55,379 --> 00:04:57,381
It would take all five...

75
00:04:57,590 --> 00:05:02,470
...Super Trooper VR Warriors
to stop your dad.

76
00:05:03,762 --> 00:05:06,265
The sincerity is oozing, Tom.

77
00:05:08,976 --> 00:05:10,561
Fuck you!

78
00:05:12,188 --> 00:05:17,193
I remember being in this hallway
thinking, "There's no road back now.

79
00:05:17,401 --> 00:05:22,907
We have started filming. Jerry
Maguire lives." It was on this shot.

80
00:05:23,115 --> 00:05:24,366
That's awesome.

81
00:05:24,700 --> 00:05:27,786
That kid couldn't wait
to say, "Fuck you."

82
00:05:28,162 --> 00:05:29,914
-Really?
-Couldn't wait.

83
00:05:30,122 --> 00:05:33,209
I remember this shot,
the day we shot it.

84
00:05:33,375 --> 00:05:37,796
We met a lot of people doing
research for the movie...

85
00:05:38,005 --> 00:05:43,302
...and many people helped. I travel led
around the NFL and met many agents.

86
00:05:43,636 --> 00:05:48,182
And almost everybody now says
they are Jerry Maguire.

87
00:05:48,349 --> 00:05:50,226
It's all based on them.

88
00:05:50,434 --> 00:05:55,731
It's the best-case scenario that
so many think that it's their story.

89
00:05:55,898 --> 00:06:00,069
But it's a fictional character
created on-screen by Tom.

90
00:06:00,653 --> 00:06:06,075
I'm very happy to say that
because it is writing of another kind.

91
00:06:06,242 --> 00:06:11,747
Just watching him do a scene
like this is cinematic literature.

92
00:06:11,914 --> 00:06:15,543
And it is a fictional character...

93
00:06:15,751 --> 00:06:21,006
...that I was so happy to watch happen
from behind the camera.

94
00:06:21,757 --> 00:06:26,011
We shot this with The Who playing,
so it feels like The Who.

95
00:06:26,178 --> 00:06:31,725
I came down to the set and was like,
"Are they filming? But there's music."

96
00:06:31,892 --> 00:06:33,978
It keeps you in the spirit.

97
00:06:35,312 --> 00:06:40,067
I began writing what they call
a mission statement, not a memo.

98
00:06:40,317 --> 00:06:43,779
A suggestion
for the future of our company.

99
00:06:45,030 --> 00:06:49,285
This is the beginning of us
playing music during the takes...

100
00:06:49,660 --> 00:06:51,745
...when we were filming.

101
00:06:52,121 --> 00:06:56,125
Originally people said,
"You're gonna cover up dialog!

102
00:06:56,292 --> 00:07:00,921
Watch out, it's terrible.
Nobody does this, it's really wrong."

103
00:07:01,130 --> 00:07:04,800
But beginning with this sequence
and a few others...

104
00:07:04,967 --> 00:07:09,888
...you began to see how playing music
would seep into the performance.

105
00:07:10,055 --> 00:07:11,390
It was helpful.

106
00:07:11,724 --> 00:07:16,270
All during rehearsal, we kept
music playing a lot during scenes.

107
00:07:16,604 --> 00:07:19,940
I loved having music play
during this sequence.

108
00:07:26,238 --> 00:07:29,825
-Oh, Dicky.
-Dicky Fox.

109
00:07:30,034 --> 00:07:31,827
Billy Wilder's role.

110
00:07:31,994 --> 00:07:35,164
"And especially you."

111
00:07:36,123 --> 00:07:38,917
We wanted Billy Wilder to play Dicky.

112
00:07:39,084 --> 00:07:42,254
He thought about it briefly and said:

113
00:07:42,588 --> 00:07:46,884
"You must find an actor to play
this part. I am not an actor.

114
00:07:47,051 --> 00:07:51,597
This is a real lesson of directing.
You must hire the actor."

115
00:07:51,764 --> 00:07:55,726
Then he saw the movie
and, happily, dug it and said:

116
00:07:55,893 --> 00:07:58,604
"Who is that guy that played my part?"

117
00:08:00,272 --> 00:08:01,273
That's great!

118
00:08:01,607 --> 00:08:04,777
I said he was a lawyer at TriStar.

119
00:08:04,943 --> 00:08:10,115
-And Billy Wilder said, "He was good."
-That's great.

120
00:08:10,991 --> 00:08:13,285
That's classic. Classic.

121
00:08:13,619 --> 00:08:17,998
Jerry Cantrell from Alice in Chains
making his screen debut.

122
00:08:18,290 --> 00:08:20,959
<i>Oh, that's where that guy's from.</i>

123
00:08:22,294 --> 00:08:25,255
That was 4 a.m.
or something, right?

124
00:08:28,717 --> 00:08:31,261
-It looks like it, Tom.
- I know.

125
00:08:31,595 --> 00:08:36,642
Jack Lord. I always wanted
to direct Jack Lord.

126
00:08:36,809 --> 00:08:39,812
I talked him into
that cameo appearance.

127
00:08:39,978 --> 00:08:42,940
Actually, we just bought a clip
from Hawaii Five-O.

128
00:08:47,986 --> 00:08:53,534
We searched for a definitive Jack Lord
as McGarrett moment, and here it is.

129
00:08:55,285 --> 00:08:56,328
Boom!

130
00:08:56,745 --> 00:08:58,580
That's great.

131
00:08:58,789 --> 00:09:01,667
This is Jerry Maguire.
Did those manuscripts--?

132
00:09:02,668 --> 00:09:04,294
"Oh, they did?"

133
00:09:04,461 --> 00:09:07,297
No, that's fine.

134
00:09:08,674 --> 00:09:12,010
-Janusz Kaminski.
-Janusz, oh.

135
00:09:12,219 --> 00:09:15,347
No one lights like him,
that's for sure.

136
00:09:17,683 --> 00:09:19,351
He's great.

137
00:09:26,066 --> 00:09:30,362
We're seeing the beginning
of Renee here, are we not?

138
00:09:30,779 --> 00:09:33,157
-There's Renee.
-And my plant.

139
00:09:33,532 --> 00:09:36,076
-There she is.
-Right, you're there.

140
00:09:37,202 --> 00:09:38,871
James L. Brooks.

141
00:09:39,079 --> 00:09:41,790
-He was there a lot.
-The gang.

142
00:09:42,541 --> 00:09:44,168
I remember this shot.

143
00:09:44,543 --> 00:09:48,005
-That was an expensive plant.
-Yes, indeed.

144
00:09:54,887 --> 00:09:58,891
When you introduced Renee
that way...

145
00:09:59,057 --> 00:10:02,853
You talked about just
wanting her in that frame.

146
00:10:03,437 --> 00:10:06,815
Written and directed
by Cameron Crowe, the man.

147
00:10:08,108 --> 00:10:11,278
-How long do you give him?
-About a week.

148
00:10:13,572 --> 00:10:17,534
-And that's the moment that turns it.
-That's great.

149
00:10:19,912 --> 00:10:23,540
It was such an emotional moment,
you in the lobby.

150
00:10:23,707 --> 00:10:28,587
Remember that long crane shot
to get down into that moment?

151
00:10:30,047 --> 00:10:32,758
-Courtney Love read for that.
-Right.

152
00:10:32,925 --> 00:10:36,762
We have tape of the audition,
and she was great.

153
00:10:36,929 --> 00:10:39,973
-Yeah, she was great.
-Very Carole Lombard.

154
00:10:40,140 --> 00:10:42,267
And there's Renee.

155
00:10:44,645 --> 00:10:50,067
-I'm sorry if I was rude just now.
-That's okay. We're in it together now.

156
00:10:50,359 --> 00:10:54,279
Why is it so easy to talk with you?
Tell me about your fiancée.

157
00:10:54,613 --> 00:10:59,618
I realized Jay Mohr's sitting
behind you. I never saw that before.

158
00:11:01,787 --> 00:11:04,498
-Lipnicki.
-Oh, God!

159
00:11:04,665 --> 00:11:06,625
How was it on that plane?

160
00:11:06,792 --> 00:11:10,963
The flying was a good day.
It was an excellent day.

161
00:11:11,129 --> 00:11:15,050
He was so cute. When he walked in,
he looked like that.

162
00:11:15,217 --> 00:11:16,635
-Sweet.
-Oh, man.

163
00:11:16,802 --> 00:11:18,637
I know, that's him.

164
00:11:18,804 --> 00:11:23,642
He put his little arms up,
and I said we had to pretend to sleep.

165
00:11:23,809 --> 00:11:28,522
And he goes, "Okay,"
then he put his arms around me...

166
00:11:28,689 --> 00:11:31,233
...tucked his head in,
closed his eyes.

167
00:11:31,567 --> 00:11:35,571
He was so professional,
it was scary, like a grown man.

168
00:11:35,737 --> 00:11:37,823
You didn't have to patronize--

169
00:11:38,073 --> 00:11:41,660
-He's such a life force.
-He's extraordinary.

170
00:11:41,827 --> 00:11:45,914
-A beautiful heart, that kid.
-I love Renee listening here.

171
00:11:46,081 --> 00:11:50,586
She is just strapped in
for the whole story. It's so great.

172
00:11:55,674 --> 00:12:01,013
One thing we worked on in the script,
it's the genius of James Brooks, is...

173
00:12:01,179 --> 00:12:04,683
...while we worked
on the script for years...

174
00:12:04,850 --> 00:12:08,645
...Jim said, "Let's put a goal
out for ourselves...

175
00:12:08,854 --> 00:12:14,026
...that this movie begins
where an '80s movie would've ended.

176
00:12:14,192 --> 00:12:19,698
The guy that finds the religion
of goodness. Let's begin with that.

177
00:12:19,948 --> 00:12:22,784
And then have him
have to battle back...

178
00:12:22,951 --> 00:12:27,205
...from what would've been the ending
of a movie 15 years ago."

179
00:12:27,414 --> 00:12:31,668
And we worked on that structure
for a long time.

180
00:12:37,674 --> 00:12:41,011
It used to be a better meal,
now it's a better life.

181
00:12:41,678 --> 00:12:44,222
-Great, Renee.
-And he's just smiling.

182
00:12:44,389 --> 00:12:49,937
-Jonathan just giving it to you.
-Yes, "Here you go."

183
00:12:50,145 --> 00:12:55,692
That's what I loved about this script.
Cameron, I remember I went nuts.

184
00:12:56,109 --> 00:12:59,279
I remember seeing Say Anything.

185
00:12:59,446 --> 00:13:05,077
And I called you that night after it.
Because we'd met earlier, before.

186
00:13:05,744 --> 00:13:09,873
I was like, "Who directed this?
Is that the same Cameron Crowe?"

187
00:13:10,082 --> 00:13:11,249
That's great.

188
00:13:11,416 --> 00:13:13,710
I was honoured to work with you...

189
00:13:13,877 --> 00:13:16,964
-Brother, it's mutual.
-...and these characters.

190
00:13:17,130 --> 00:13:20,842
You read the script in zero time,
called and said:

191
00:13:21,009 --> 00:13:25,347
-"Let's talk about it. Jerry Maguire."
-Let's go, brother.

192
00:13:28,767 --> 00:13:30,978
Listen, Dorothy. Dorothy?

193
00:13:31,395 --> 00:13:34,940
While I go look for him,
grab this gentleman here.

194
00:13:37,275 --> 00:13:39,111
So cute.

195
00:13:43,156 --> 00:13:46,034
You scared me. You scared me!

196
00:13:46,243 --> 00:13:49,663
-Don't do that again, ever!
-Okay, Mommy.

197
00:13:49,913 --> 00:13:52,666
Ever, ever, ever! Okay? Ever!

198
00:13:52,916 --> 00:13:54,251
Dorothy?

199
00:13:55,210 --> 00:14:00,757
Now, how do you catch that entire
harried, loving mother feeling?

200
00:14:02,926 --> 00:14:04,845
Accident.

201
00:14:05,721 --> 00:14:07,806
-You did?
-Yeah.

202
00:14:12,436 --> 00:14:14,146
What a day.

203
00:14:16,815 --> 00:14:19,067
That was a huge day.

204
00:14:19,234 --> 00:14:21,611
That was a great day.

205
00:14:21,778 --> 00:14:25,824
You just stood there
and had this smile on your face.

206
00:14:25,991 --> 00:14:31,329
You knew I was scared to death.
It was the first scene that we did...

207
00:14:31,663 --> 00:14:35,834
...and I'm scared to death.
You just had this--

208
00:14:36,001 --> 00:14:40,630
-You were just so right there.
-You were on fire.

209
00:14:40,797 --> 00:14:44,176
You were the greatest guy
on the planet that day.

210
00:14:44,342 --> 00:14:49,848
It wasn't hard! Like, he walks away,
and there was some goofy look.

211
00:14:50,223 --> 00:14:54,978
It wasn't too hard to play
that day, I have to say.

212
00:14:55,228 --> 00:14:59,399
But since I've gotten to know
you better-- But on that day...

213
00:15:00,067 --> 00:15:05,030
-It was a beautiful day.
-This was the day where I said to Tom:

214
00:15:05,197 --> 00:15:08,825
"Add a 'whoo' in the middle
of what you're saying."

215
00:15:08,992 --> 00:15:13,205
He said, "Okay."
And I thought, "This is really fun."

216
00:15:13,371 --> 00:15:18,877
Then I get to watch little Jonathan
swinging between you guys. It was...

217
00:15:19,211 --> 00:15:21,296
...yeah, so great.

218
00:15:25,884 --> 00:15:30,013
-Here's the real Renee, right there.
-That's Renee!

219
00:15:30,222 --> 00:15:33,725
-Shut up!
-That is so you!

220
00:15:33,934 --> 00:15:35,894
That's our girl.

221
00:15:38,897 --> 00:15:41,942
-That's so great!
-That's so her.

222
00:15:43,860 --> 00:15:47,864
-Laurel, the buzz killer.
-"There's my sister, Laurel."

223
00:15:49,783 --> 00:15:51,034
...Dorothy.

224
00:15:51,660 --> 00:15:53,078
Pleasure.

225
00:15:54,037 --> 00:15:55,580
Bye.

226
00:15:56,790 --> 00:16:00,085
-Look at those looks.
-Oh, I love it.

227
00:16:00,252 --> 00:16:02,087
That's great.

228
00:16:03,088 --> 00:16:07,175
-So many rich characters.
-My wife, Nancy Wilson's score.

229
00:16:07,342 --> 00:16:09,094
-No kidding.
-Beautiful.

230
00:16:09,261 --> 00:16:12,889
Really caught the feeling of love
starting to blossom...

231
00:16:13,056 --> 00:16:15,350
...before either of them knew it.

232
00:16:21,064 --> 00:16:22,732
The dog!

233
00:16:22,899 --> 00:16:25,068
-Okay!
-Kelly!

234
00:16:26,820 --> 00:16:30,073
Sooner or later we'll have to stop!

235
00:16:30,448 --> 00:16:34,369
Aerosmith, wasn't it?
Aerosmith, we played?

236
00:16:34,744 --> 00:16:37,914
Did you really? Oh, you're kidding.

237
00:16:38,081 --> 00:16:42,085
The dog! "You're doing it wrong.
It's the wrong position!"

238
00:16:43,336 --> 00:16:48,633
I can't watch that scene.
I can't watch that scene!

239
00:16:48,800 --> 00:16:51,011
-Why?
-I've never been able to.

240
00:16:51,303 --> 00:16:53,805
Tell us about that, Renee.

241
00:16:57,267 --> 00:17:00,812
Let's rewind this scene.
Let's dissect it.

242
00:17:00,979 --> 00:17:05,317
-What troubles you?
-It's too much information for me.

243
00:17:05,650 --> 00:17:10,614
Too much information
I never need to know.

244
00:17:12,032 --> 00:17:15,285
"You don't have to tell me everything."

245
00:17:15,619 --> 00:17:18,079
-That was classic.
-Great writing.

246
00:17:18,288 --> 00:17:20,624
"If you ever wanted..."

247
00:17:23,335 --> 00:17:25,086
That's great.

248
00:17:25,670 --> 00:17:29,174
We did this the night before,
trying to figure out...

249
00:17:29,341 --> 00:17:34,387
...how do we just show two people,
post-sex, just kind of hanging out?

250
00:17:34,763 --> 00:17:39,226
And we just put them at the table.
This is great.

251
00:17:44,022 --> 00:17:48,401
Mark Pellington, great director,
good friend of mine...

252
00:17:48,777 --> 00:17:51,154
-...playing Dooler.
-There they are.

253
00:17:52,197 --> 00:17:55,951
Tim McDonald, the first guy
when he walks in--

254
00:17:56,117 --> 00:17:59,246
Excuse me.
Eric Stoltz, ladies and gentlemen.

255
00:17:59,412 --> 00:18:04,251
-Do you make fun of him too?
-No. There's still time, though.

256
00:18:09,172 --> 00:18:11,049
This is what it's all about, man.

257
00:18:12,676 --> 00:18:14,302
Everybody loves you.

258
00:18:16,554 --> 00:18:18,431
Pisses me off!

259
00:18:20,267 --> 00:18:24,896
This guy's from the This is Elvis
film. "Whether you're young or old."

260
00:18:27,482 --> 00:18:31,569
...Jerry Maguire will still
be the king of rock 'n' roll.

261
00:18:32,696 --> 00:18:38,076
-Little black book.
-When I think of him, my heart pounds.

262
00:18:40,996 --> 00:18:46,167
We went too far with the bachelorette
film. We have about 50 minutes...

263
00:18:47,085 --> 00:18:49,546
...of women talking about Jerry.

264
00:18:49,754 --> 00:18:52,757
I hear, "I was in Jerry Maguire.
I got cut."

265
00:18:52,924 --> 00:18:57,512
From the film? From the
bachelorette film. That's funny.

266
00:18:57,679 --> 00:18:58,847
He's almost phobic.

267
00:18:59,055 --> 00:19:03,601
Jerry is great at friendship,
he's just bad at intimacy.

268
00:19:03,810 --> 00:19:06,938
-He can't be alone.
-He can't be alone.

269
00:19:07,147 --> 00:19:12,277
-He can't say, "I love you."
-He's an agent. He lies.

270
00:19:12,694 --> 00:19:16,031
-Love her.
-She's ready to fistfight.

271
00:19:16,197 --> 00:19:18,742
-Love you too.
-Love you.

272
00:19:19,034 --> 00:19:20,076
I love you, man.

273
00:19:23,621 --> 00:19:26,958
There's a seething wrongness
in the room.

274
00:19:29,294 --> 00:19:31,171
That's insane.

275
00:19:32,964 --> 00:19:35,842
A shout out to
Joe Hutshing, the editor.

276
00:19:36,051 --> 00:19:39,971
Just did an amazing job on this movie.

277
00:19:41,014 --> 00:19:45,685
If you really think about it,
the beginning of this movie...

278
00:19:45,852 --> 00:19:48,855
...Is all characters,
setting up who Jerry is.

279
00:19:49,022 --> 00:19:52,567
-Behaviour.
-Behaviour, acting and editing.

280
00:19:52,734 --> 00:19:55,320
Regina King, ladies and gentlemen.

281
00:19:55,487 --> 00:19:58,031
-Tyson, no!
-Okay, Mommy.

282
00:19:58,281 --> 00:20:01,493
-Tyson, hello.
-Long time no see!

283
00:20:02,327 --> 00:20:06,664
-The boy's cute too. He was awesome.
-He was great.

284
00:20:06,831 --> 00:20:10,668
-In the bathtub scene.
-Tyson destroyed that set.

285
00:20:10,835 --> 00:20:13,338
-He was genius.
-He loved it!

286
00:20:14,172 --> 00:20:15,715
-Knock.
-Pleasure.

287
00:20:18,843 --> 00:20:22,847
-Oh, she's great.
-She's great, Jay Mohr was great.

288
00:20:23,348 --> 00:20:25,141
He rocked.

289
00:20:25,558 --> 00:20:27,560
The finger's here.

290
00:20:28,520 --> 00:20:31,856
We are just counting down
to Rod Tidwell now.

291
00:20:32,023 --> 00:20:36,694
-This is the Tidwell countdown.
-Oh, we can feel Cuba coming!

292
00:20:39,614 --> 00:20:42,575
-Wow.
-He and I majored in marketing.

293
00:20:42,826 --> 00:20:43,952
We came to play!

294
00:20:44,244 --> 00:20:46,204
So sweet.

295
00:20:48,289 --> 00:20:50,166
My little family.

296
00:20:50,542 --> 00:20:52,836
An agent we interviewed said:

297
00:20:53,002 --> 00:20:56,714
"Fear the protective wife most of all.

298
00:20:56,881 --> 00:21:00,135
She'll be the one that'll
make you do your job...

299
00:21:00,301 --> 00:21:03,596
...more than you ever dreamed
you'd have to."

300
00:21:03,763 --> 00:21:08,685
And that was how to bring love
and drive to that character.

301
00:21:08,852 --> 00:21:12,313
That's the beauty of what Regina did.

302
00:21:12,689 --> 00:21:17,068
There's so much love in what she does
yet she drives Jerry hard.

303
00:21:17,235 --> 00:21:19,028
Riding him hard.

304
00:21:19,195 --> 00:21:24,409
Now here's Jay Mohr being given
the gift of really just...

305
00:21:24,742 --> 00:21:28,204
-Slam-dunking me.
-...whomping Tom!

306
00:21:29,664 --> 00:21:30,999
And loving it.

307
00:21:31,207 --> 00:21:35,795
Jay Mohr, Saturday Night Live
just a few seasons back.

308
00:21:36,004 --> 00:21:40,884
Now you get to whomp on Tom
on the major screen!

309
00:21:42,802 --> 00:21:46,764
Cut to the water glass
with the beads of sweat.

310
00:21:47,098 --> 00:21:48,808
That was awesome.

311
00:21:49,893 --> 00:21:54,355
I like the cut to the water and ice,
hearing the ice in the mix.

312
00:21:55,982 --> 00:22:00,612
I love this scene.
"Could you get past yourself?”

313
00:22:00,820 --> 00:22:02,614
-You'll lose.
-You want smaller.

314
00:22:04,782 --> 00:22:09,078
-Just kicks it.
-"Get past yourself for a second.”

315
00:22:09,370 --> 00:22:13,291
I love the idea of someone
being an asshole to you...

316
00:22:13,666 --> 00:22:16,169
...begging you for sympathy.

317
00:22:17,754 --> 00:22:21,382
Here's the fall.
We did takes where I don't fall.

318
00:22:21,716 --> 00:22:26,846
Then Cameron came over and said,
"Why don't you fall on your face?"

319
00:22:27,305 --> 00:22:32,018
-That's great.
- I said, "All right. Sounds like fun."”

320
00:22:32,185 --> 00:22:36,940
He sort of animated
the subtext a little bit...

321
00:22:37,148 --> 00:22:41,194
...of what's happening here.
It was a genius day.

322
00:22:45,323 --> 00:22:48,409
Remember the talks
about this phone battle?

323
00:22:48,743 --> 00:22:52,705
The war that was built up
and built up.

324
00:22:52,872 --> 00:22:56,417
-The whole idea was to have a duel.
-Just stacked it.

325
00:22:56,751 --> 00:22:59,837
Just bring the phone duel on.

326
00:23:01,798 --> 00:23:03,675
And bring me my numbers!

327
00:23:04,842 --> 00:23:07,679
He's just getting crushed.

328
00:23:07,971 --> 00:23:11,891
He had a meltdown.
I've talked to Doritos about you.

329
00:23:12,141 --> 00:23:14,561
They're interested. Talk to Rick.

330
00:23:15,895 --> 00:23:19,190
These guys together that day.
It was insane.

331
00:23:19,357 --> 00:23:21,693
-Remember?
-Insane in that room.

332
00:23:21,859 --> 00:23:26,155
On another chapter of this DVD,
you'll see complete takes.

333
00:23:26,322 --> 00:23:31,494
These guys are ripping, both of them,
for minutes upon minutes.

334
00:23:31,661 --> 00:23:34,581
I'm gonna make this easy for you.

335
00:23:34,831 --> 00:23:37,709
Just what does your heart tell you?

336
00:23:40,003 --> 00:23:41,337
Sorry to hear that.

337
00:23:48,136 --> 00:23:53,683
A shout out to Betsy Heimann. I love
how you're dressed. Is that crazy?

338
00:23:53,850 --> 00:23:59,022
-No, I love it too.
-It is the perfect look for Dorothy.

339
00:23:59,188 --> 00:24:04,777
She dressed that way, she's gonna
make a stand today. It's so great.

340
00:24:06,946 --> 00:24:09,365
Perfect style, I thought.

341
00:24:09,741 --> 00:24:11,868
-Drew Bledsoe.
-Drew!

342
00:24:13,870 --> 00:24:16,331
Bob Sugar? He's...

343
00:24:16,581 --> 00:24:19,042
He's entertaining, funny.

344
00:24:19,250 --> 00:24:23,171
I don't know what it's like
to be black? I'm Mr. Black People!

345
00:24:24,589 --> 00:24:29,093
Now, this is one of the (gifts,
again, the gifts of Tom...

346
00:24:29,260 --> 00:24:31,095
-...to his director.
-Go ahead.

347
00:24:31,304 --> 00:24:35,308
I yelled that out, to just say that.
Just, "Try this!"

348
00:24:35,683 --> 00:24:37,143
You blasted it out.

349
00:24:37,310 --> 00:24:42,148
We'd do takes. You'd fire dialog
at me as we ripped through it.

350
00:24:42,690 --> 00:24:45,318
And we dig that about you, Cameron.

351
00:24:45,693 --> 00:24:51,032
Writing on the fly. It's like playing
jazz. That's what it feels like.

352
00:24:51,324 --> 00:24:54,410
-And he's riffing.
-Just going. I love that.

353
00:24:55,203 --> 00:24:58,373
-Look at that, love that.
- I love that moment.

354
00:24:58,706 --> 00:25:02,794
-Okay, well, this happened to me.
-This is classic.

355
00:25:02,960 --> 00:25:07,382
With an actress or something?
You're kidding.

356
00:25:12,970 --> 00:25:17,100
She had taken the part,
then she called me back...

357
00:25:17,308 --> 00:25:22,772
...to say she couldn't do it, and she
was heartbroken. And this happened.

358
00:25:23,106 --> 00:25:25,900
And it hurt like it hurts Jerry.

359
00:25:27,944 --> 00:25:32,323
Think she regrets it? Actresses
you work with go on to be okay.

360
00:25:32,657 --> 00:25:35,993
You're very kind, but--
Oh, there he is!

361
00:25:38,830 --> 00:25:42,625
Bob Sugar says
I'm missing out by being with you.

362
00:25:42,875 --> 00:25:47,046
-That's how I'm doing.
-That's why I'm calling.

363
00:25:47,255 --> 00:25:51,384
No, I hear that.
But do you truly hear what I'm saying?

364
00:25:55,638 --> 00:25:57,265
Sweet.

365
00:25:57,598 --> 00:26:01,352
When you shot your stuff,
I had already wrapped.

366
00:26:01,686 --> 00:26:05,189
That's so funny.
You were in England, right?

367
00:26:05,356 --> 00:26:10,069
-This is the last two days of filming?
-It was.

368
00:26:10,236 --> 00:26:13,239
Out there in Thousand Oaks.

369
00:26:13,823 --> 00:26:15,700
So insane.

370
00:26:16,242 --> 00:26:19,328
I am a valuable commodity!

371
00:26:19,579 --> 00:26:25,001
I see a dude out to kill me,
I tell myself, "Catch the ball."

372
00:26:25,251 --> 00:26:28,087
Touchdown! I make miracles happen.

373
00:26:28,713 --> 00:26:33,384
Thank you, Janusz, for that shot.
And thank you, Cuba!

374
00:26:34,177 --> 00:26:37,388
I went to Arizona State!
I'm a Sun Devil!

375
00:26:39,891 --> 00:26:44,937
-Did you get that painting?
-No. There was a lot I was gonna get--

376
00:26:45,104 --> 00:26:48,024
-The ants, I love.
-The ants.

377
00:26:50,651 --> 00:26:52,320
Aries.

378
00:26:53,905 --> 00:26:56,491
-Hello, brother Maguire.
-Hello, Tee Pee.

379
00:27:00,244 --> 00:27:02,914
"Do not arrest this man."

380
00:27:03,331 --> 00:27:06,751
Where is the Waterbed Warehouse?

381
00:27:06,918 --> 00:27:11,255
- I didn't get any of that.
-That's wrong!

382
00:27:11,422 --> 00:27:15,760
I was told I was gonna get it,
then it just went away.

383
00:27:15,927 --> 00:27:20,348
-Somebody's got it. If you have it...
-Please, send it.

384
00:27:20,723 --> 00:27:23,559
But I like you. Yes, I like you.

385
00:27:25,770 --> 00:27:29,106
-This is music you found.
-Where did it come from?

386
00:27:29,315 --> 00:27:32,652
In rehearsal, I played it
and Cameron said:

387
00:27:32,819 --> 00:27:36,113
"Remember to bring it that day,"
and we had it.

388
00:27:36,322 --> 00:27:39,826
-Where did we rehearse?
-At Sony, in the offices.

389
00:27:39,992 --> 00:27:43,830
What can I do for you?
Just tell me, what can I do?

390
00:27:47,333 --> 00:27:50,044
-That boy was so cute.
-Beautiful.

391
00:27:50,211 --> 00:27:51,546
-You ready?
-Ready.

392
00:27:51,796 --> 00:27:53,840
Making sure you are, brother.

393
00:27:54,632 --> 00:27:56,092
Here it is:

394
00:27:57,969 --> 00:27:59,637
Show me the money.

395
00:28:01,138 --> 00:28:05,643
Right behind me!
He throws his hands up.

396
00:28:06,853 --> 00:28:12,191
He's like, "That was it. That's the
line!" He's got the football going.

397
00:28:14,652 --> 00:28:16,654
He's got the football going!

398
00:28:16,863 --> 00:28:21,158
Yes. Well, this was all
in the script, wasn't it?

399
00:28:23,661 --> 00:28:26,873
You two yelled things
off camera to me...

400
00:28:27,081 --> 00:28:29,667
...while I shot my end of it.

401
00:28:29,834 --> 00:28:33,754
You're on the phone, Cameron
yells to you, you yell to me.

402
00:28:37,592 --> 00:28:39,510
That's so brilliant!

403
00:28:40,011 --> 00:28:44,015
-Oh, God!
-Look at that--

404
00:28:44,181 --> 00:28:49,020
-That line has haunted me ever since.
-For the rest of your life.

405
00:28:49,186 --> 00:28:51,606
I could be at a funeral...

406
00:28:51,814 --> 00:28:55,234
...you'll hear some prick go,
"Show me the money!"

407
00:28:55,568 --> 00:28:58,779
-Shut up!
-"You're my motherfucker."

408
00:28:59,196 --> 00:29:03,034
You know,
with all due respect, Cuba...

409
00:29:03,826 --> 00:29:06,704
...I think you sort of
built that moment...

410
00:29:06,913 --> 00:29:10,708
-...to such a huge, beautiful degree.
-Look at Tom!

411
00:29:11,125 --> 00:29:13,628
-You know?
-Let it fly, man!

412
00:29:13,794 --> 00:29:17,882
"Show me the money! You know?!"

413
00:29:21,761 --> 00:29:25,056
We are so lucky
that we have tape...

414
00:29:25,222 --> 00:29:30,686
...of the birth of "Show me the money,"
which will be part of this.

415
00:29:30,853 --> 00:29:35,816
It's just what came from you and Tom
as you rehearsed, and it grew.

416
00:29:36,025 --> 00:29:40,154
You had this music in your head.
And you were moving...

417
00:29:40,321 --> 00:29:44,659
...and doing the music
and the dialog at the same time.

418
00:29:44,825 --> 00:29:46,744
An amazing piece of film.

419
00:29:46,911 --> 00:29:49,705
I love when you do that
"flip out" thing.

420
00:29:49,872 --> 00:29:53,042
Nobody had ever seen you
act like that.

421
00:29:53,250 --> 00:29:55,753
Tom's a little crazy on the set.

422
00:29:55,920 --> 00:30:00,883
-You'd never let go like that before.
- I never had a character.

423
00:30:01,092 --> 00:30:04,303
They saw A Few Good Men,
they saw Rain Man...

424
00:30:04,679 --> 00:30:08,599
...even with Paul Newman.
Then you were like, "My balls are out...

425
00:30:08,766 --> 00:30:11,936
...step on them
and pass them to the next person.”

426
00:30:12,103 --> 00:30:15,606
-It's fun.
-It was awesome.

427
00:30:18,067 --> 00:30:21,404
In fact, I'm starting a new company...

428
00:30:21,654 --> 00:30:24,532
...and the fish will come with me.

429
00:30:24,699 --> 00:30:29,996
The goldfish. Cameron was obsessed
with his goldfish.

430
00:30:30,663 --> 00:30:33,833
You remember the package
that it came in?

431
00:30:34,875 --> 00:30:39,755
-Even the fishes run.
-It took a few takes to get that.

432
00:30:39,922 --> 00:30:44,427
-I love when you seal the bag in.
-He did it with such care.

433
00:30:44,760 --> 00:30:46,262
His only friend.

434
00:30:47,888 --> 00:30:49,890
That's classic.

435
00:30:52,935 --> 00:30:56,105
...real and fun and inspiring...

436
00:30:59,025 --> 00:31:02,069
She's so cute.

437
00:31:02,361 --> 00:31:06,824
That line is from Nancy Wilson,
the great Nancy Wilson:

438
00:31:06,991 --> 00:31:10,995
"Looking for truth
in this godforsaken business."

439
00:31:18,794 --> 00:31:20,671
That's great.

440
00:31:21,088 --> 00:31:23,924
Jann Wenner walking away.

441
00:31:25,718 --> 00:31:27,803
This is embarrassing.

442
00:31:28,262 --> 00:31:29,305
Damn.

443
00:31:29,680 --> 00:31:33,434
-But you got your fish, honey.
-That's right.

444
00:31:35,895 --> 00:31:37,605
Wendy.

445
00:31:40,024 --> 00:31:43,402
How genius is that?
He's got the fish in the bag.

446
00:31:43,736 --> 00:31:45,863
I mean, who thinks of that?

447
00:31:46,030 --> 00:31:47,364
But not Wendy.

448
00:31:47,865 --> 00:31:49,700
You don't have Wendy.

449
00:31:50,409 --> 00:31:51,702
Look.

450
00:31:52,870 --> 00:31:58,209
-The fish in the bag, the whole time.
-He's gotta walk out by himself.

451
00:31:58,667 --> 00:32:00,711
He's got the fish.

452
00:32:00,878 --> 00:32:03,964
-He's got Swim-Along.
-There we go, Dorothy.

453
00:32:05,049 --> 00:32:07,218
Did she hit the coffee yet?

454
00:32:10,096 --> 00:32:15,017
- I don't think that made it.
-Yeah, we had a version...

455
00:32:15,226 --> 00:32:18,104
-...where she spills coffee.
-"Right now?"

456
00:32:25,945 --> 00:32:27,738
Bye.

457
00:32:29,907 --> 00:32:34,870
Your face, in this scene, said it
all. That's why you get paid okay.

458
00:32:36,122 --> 00:32:39,917
-Really.
-Oh, look at Renee. Look at Renee.

459
00:32:40,084 --> 00:32:45,422
You dream about having chemistry
with your lead actors.

460
00:32:47,758 --> 00:32:49,343
Pretty awesome.

461
00:32:50,177 --> 00:32:51,762
Pretty awesome.

462
00:32:52,263 --> 00:32:53,305
What was it like--7?

463
00:32:53,639 --> 00:32:56,350
I love this, everyone goes
back to work.

464
00:32:59,145 --> 00:33:01,105
"Who's got my memo?"

465
00:33:01,272 --> 00:33:04,942
-Whatever, life goes on.
-Huge moment and then--

466
00:33:05,192 --> 00:33:07,570
Sure, yes, medical.

467
00:33:09,947 --> 00:33:10,948
Hot.

468
00:33:11,282 --> 00:33:15,786
Is it harder or easier to do
a scene with a lot of extras...

469
00:33:15,953 --> 00:33:17,246
...watching you act?

470
00:33:17,413 --> 00:33:20,958
-It was really helpful.
-Yeah, I liked it.

471
00:33:21,125 --> 00:33:23,752
It depends what you're doing.

472
00:33:24,879 --> 00:33:27,506
In a funny scene,
it's like an audience.

473
00:33:27,715 --> 00:33:31,260
If you're doing something
emotional and tender...

474
00:33:31,594 --> 00:33:36,932
-...with people looking, that's weird.
-Show me the money--

475
00:33:40,060 --> 00:33:41,979
-Oh, yeah.
-Oh, yeah.

476
00:33:55,034 --> 00:33:57,203
I wonder what he said.

477
00:33:57,620 --> 00:34:00,247
My favourite aunt is hearing-impaired.

478
00:34:00,497 --> 00:34:03,834
He just said, "You complete me."

479
00:34:05,836 --> 00:34:07,755
She's scared to death.

480
00:34:09,882 --> 00:34:14,261
-It's been a bad day.
-Jerry's trying to grasp that concept.

481
00:34:14,595 --> 00:34:17,932
-Jerry's trying to feel.
-"You complete me."

482
00:34:18,098 --> 00:34:22,603
What exactly--? I kind of know
but I'm reaching...

483
00:34:25,773 --> 00:34:29,109
This-- Oh, this was great stuff.

484
00:34:29,276 --> 00:34:32,112
Look at that, look where it goes.

485
00:34:32,321 --> 00:34:37,284
It goes from in that elevator,
that moment, to this.

486
00:34:37,701 --> 00:34:39,954
-Same movie.
-I know. Shift.

487
00:34:40,120 --> 00:34:43,123
-It never happens.
-This screenplay is...

488
00:34:43,290 --> 00:34:46,627
When have you read
something like that?

489
00:34:46,835 --> 00:34:49,713
-Hi, Mom.
-Oh, that's your mom!

490
00:34:49,922 --> 00:34:52,925
These are mostly comediennes that--

491
00:34:53,133 --> 00:34:56,804
There's Winnie Holzman, who wrote
My So-Called Life.

492
00:34:57,012 --> 00:35:01,016
I love that line she has,
"All this chocolate-eating!"

493
00:35:01,183 --> 00:35:04,228
-She wrote that, that's Winnie.
-I love it.

494
00:35:06,647 --> 00:35:07,690
I...

495
00:35:08,732 --> 00:35:10,317
...love this scene.

496
00:35:12,569 --> 00:35:14,738
- I love Bonnie Hunt.
-Love her.

497
00:35:14,905 --> 00:35:16,699
-She's awesome.
-Love her.

498
00:35:16,907 --> 00:35:19,952
Here's another side of Renee
you meet.

499
00:35:20,119 --> 00:35:22,204
Dorothy, I should say.

500
00:35:26,583 --> 00:35:29,253
It's the steel in Dorothy.

501
00:35:29,837 --> 00:35:32,256
And the love for the son.

502
00:35:32,589 --> 00:35:35,843
It's great what you did here, Renee.

503
00:35:36,010 --> 00:35:39,972
Oh, that's that day.
The first thing that I did.

504
00:35:41,640 --> 00:35:45,227
Function, function.
Forward motion is everything.

505
00:35:45,436 --> 00:35:47,938
Cush saves all.

506
00:35:49,690 --> 00:35:51,150
Oh, God.

507
00:35:54,111 --> 00:35:55,612
Oh, God!

508
00:35:58,240 --> 00:36:01,952
- I was trying to sleep with you.
-Well, it worked.

509
00:36:02,244 --> 00:36:07,374
And I will not let you fail.
You are Jerry Ma-fucking-guire!

510
00:36:08,042 --> 00:36:09,710
Go, Kelly.

511
00:36:13,213 --> 00:36:15,049
That's awesome.

512
00:36:20,179 --> 00:36:25,476
-Who said anything about "loser"?
-Mistake. Wrong word! Let's leave.

513
00:36:27,394 --> 00:36:30,439
The way Kelly says,
"Jerry Ma-fucking-guire."

514
00:36:30,773 --> 00:36:33,692
It just sets it off, it really does.

515
00:36:34,234 --> 00:36:37,863
-Puts her whole gig--
-Here we come, Beau Bridges.

516
00:36:38,072 --> 00:36:42,159
-Oh, that's right, bloody beer.
-Dropping in for some love.

517
00:36:54,129 --> 00:36:55,464
That's awesome.

518
00:36:56,965 --> 00:36:58,675
That is awesome.

519
00:36:58,842 --> 00:37:01,595
-Would you like a bloody beer?
-I'm fine.

520
00:37:02,096 --> 00:37:05,140
-Beer and tomato juice.
-"Beer and tomato juice.”

521
00:37:05,307 --> 00:37:10,813
That's a shout out to my buddy Kelly
Curtis, inventor of the bloody beer.

522
00:37:11,688 --> 00:37:13,690
So hey, Kelly.

523
00:37:16,443 --> 00:37:19,363
We decided to stay with you.

524
00:37:26,036 --> 00:37:29,206
How fast can you hug him
after he says it?

525
00:37:29,373 --> 00:37:33,377
Don't hesitate, as soon
as it comes out, hit him.

526
00:37:35,838 --> 00:37:38,215
Watch Beau Bridges.
Watch his drink.

527
00:37:38,382 --> 00:37:43,387
That's a Tom moment right there,
you just saw the real Tom Cruise.

528
00:37:44,304 --> 00:37:47,975
You've done it once,
you've done it a thousand times.

529
00:37:48,142 --> 00:37:51,645
Every time I see that,
I go, "That's Tom."

530
00:37:52,062 --> 00:37:54,064
That's the boy.

531
00:37:54,690 --> 00:37:59,987
I think there's another Tom moment
coming up in a second.

532
00:38:00,195 --> 00:38:04,908
On every shoot, you get into a zone.
It takes a while sometimes...

533
00:38:05,075 --> 00:38:06,910
...but when you're there,
you're there.

534
00:38:07,077 --> 00:38:09,371
Anything you say or do, it's in.

535
00:38:09,746 --> 00:38:12,791
-You just bring it.
-Yeah, it just comes.

536
00:38:13,041 --> 00:38:14,168
Here it comes.

537
00:38:14,334 --> 00:38:16,086
Janusz, lighting there.

538
00:38:16,253 --> 00:38:18,297
Here we go!

539
00:38:19,882 --> 00:38:21,758
There's the boy.

540
00:38:24,303 --> 00:38:28,891
Ladies and gentlemen,
Tom Cruise, Hollywood, California.

541
00:38:36,982 --> 00:38:40,110
You driving to the studio,
today, right?

542
00:38:42,613 --> 00:38:44,281
Oh, that's great.

543
00:38:45,115 --> 00:38:47,826
I love when he does, "I'm free!"

544
00:38:49,578 --> 00:38:54,124
-Nothing half-assed. Nothing ever.
-That's right. That's true.

545
00:38:54,291 --> 00:38:56,168
Not even that.

546
00:38:58,629 --> 00:39:01,715
He hadn't played hockey in years.

547
00:39:01,924 --> 00:39:05,802
He scored a goal.
But he almost broke his neck.

548
00:39:05,969 --> 00:39:09,640
-I was like, "That's Tom."
-Night before the shoot...

549
00:39:09,806 --> 00:39:13,185
...he's on top of some guy, fighting.
I'm thinking:

550
00:39:13,352 --> 00:39:16,939
"I don't want to show up
bloody and bruised.”

551
00:39:17,689 --> 00:39:20,609
-That's him, man.
-Nothing half-assed.

552
00:39:20,776 --> 00:39:23,237
Always balls out. It's awesome.

553
00:39:23,570 --> 00:39:26,532
That's why you are where you are.

554
00:39:26,740 --> 00:39:29,701
That's why friends like him.
So I hear.

555
00:39:32,079 --> 00:39:33,580
Look at this.

556
00:39:35,123 --> 00:39:37,209
I re-signed Cush. We're set.

557
00:39:37,459 --> 00:39:40,879
-I am so happy for you.
-Happy for us.

558
00:39:41,129 --> 00:39:44,383
Happy for us. Okay, happy for us.

559
00:39:44,716 --> 00:39:47,261
Rod, being at the draft is good.

560
00:39:50,889 --> 00:39:55,310
I should tell this story.
This scene was much simpler.

561
00:39:57,271 --> 00:39:59,314
Tom said, "I'm a father.

562
00:39:59,690 --> 00:40:05,028
And there's aspects of repartee
with a kid, with your son...

563
00:40:05,195 --> 00:40:08,323
...that just-- I think we
can get more here."

564
00:40:08,657 --> 00:40:12,286
So we dug in, and Jonathan himself--

565
00:40:12,619 --> 00:40:14,913
He came to the set one day saying:

566
00:40:15,080 --> 00:40:17,708
"The human head
weighs eight pounds.”

567
00:40:17,874 --> 00:40:20,919
-Is that true?
-Are you serious?

568
00:40:21,128 --> 00:40:23,338
So the two things came together.

569
00:40:27,050 --> 00:40:29,177
Well, I wrote that--

570
00:40:30,220 --> 00:40:32,222
The last one is yours, huh?

571
00:40:32,598 --> 00:40:37,227
We combined the two and wrote
this scene the night before.

572
00:40:37,894 --> 00:40:41,898
Did it completely fresh. It's one
of my favourite scenes.

573
00:40:42,065 --> 00:40:44,693
And there's a moment here...

574
00:40:45,360 --> 00:40:48,864
...where Renee watches Tom
walk off...

575
00:40:49,072 --> 00:40:51,783
...and they see a life
they haven't had.

576
00:40:51,992 --> 00:40:55,912
-That's Dennis Fitzgerald.
-The stand-in.

577
00:40:56,163 --> 00:40:57,623
Our stand-ins.

578
00:40:57,789 --> 00:41:03,211
-This shot, Renee, you watching...
- I know, I love this.

579
00:41:03,378 --> 00:41:05,964
...will kill me for all time.

580
00:41:06,173 --> 00:41:09,968
Look at the two of them
look at each other.

581
00:41:10,135 --> 00:41:13,263
Cute. I shake your hand
and then leave.

582
00:41:13,597 --> 00:41:17,017
Leave a brother out in the cold.
That's all right.

583
00:41:17,184 --> 00:41:19,978
- I know he's coming home.
-Look at that.

584
00:41:20,187 --> 00:41:23,231
-"I'm a Sun Devil.”
-Sun Devil.

585
00:41:23,774 --> 00:41:26,443
-This is great.
-This is classic.

586
00:41:26,610 --> 00:41:28,320
Are you Hootie?

587
00:41:31,573 --> 00:41:35,077
And after this scene,
I really had that happen.

588
00:41:35,285 --> 00:41:38,830
Some kid came up to me,
"Hey, aren't you Hootie?"

589
00:41:39,039 --> 00:41:41,124
While we were filming the movie!
He hadn't seen it.

590
00:41:41,291 --> 00:41:44,544
I was, like, "Oh, this is so funny."

591
00:41:44,753 --> 00:41:48,840
If you see it in Spain, the kid says,
"Are you Ice-T?"

592
00:41:49,091 --> 00:41:51,593
-Really?
-They change it to Ice-T.

593
00:41:51,802 --> 00:41:53,637
Oh, that's great.

594
00:41:57,099 --> 00:42:00,227
I love that one. The mom and son.

595
00:42:01,228 --> 00:42:05,315
Why am I here? It's like I'm
five years late for the prom.

596
00:42:05,649 --> 00:42:10,821
-Nobody gives a damn about me.
-Let's walk through this lobby.

597
00:42:10,987 --> 00:42:16,326
I want all the media and player reps
to see you for what you are:

598
00:42:16,660 --> 00:42:17,869
"Okay."

599
00:42:20,622 --> 00:42:24,251
-This is good, more.
-You remember that? Bring it.

600
00:42:24,584 --> 00:42:29,798
Cameron said, "Use your hands or
something. Make him keep talking."

601
00:42:30,173 --> 00:42:35,178
- I love Rod Tidwell.
-See the walk. Look at the walk.

602
00:42:35,345 --> 00:42:39,182
I have a tape at home of me
in my driveway practising...

603
00:42:39,349 --> 00:42:42,060
...until I had the walk that I liked.

604
00:42:42,310 --> 00:42:43,937
Look at this.

605
00:42:44,354 --> 00:42:48,984
-I love Rod Tidwell.
-He's not listening, but he is.

606
00:42:49,192 --> 00:42:52,612
The walk is just--
Cuba, the walk is--

607
00:42:52,779 --> 00:42:53,905
Classic.

608
00:42:54,072 --> 00:42:56,199
It's a thing of beauty.

609
00:43:02,164 --> 00:43:04,833
-How are you?
-Good, hey.

610
00:43:05,041 --> 00:43:07,294
"Yeah, listen to Jerry."

611
00:43:08,754 --> 00:43:10,380
-Good?
-Great, baby.

612
00:43:11,089 --> 00:43:14,217
-Mike Tirico, ESPN.
-Yeah, that's right.

613
00:43:15,927 --> 00:43:18,597
This is, like, guy-dream come true.

614
00:43:18,805 --> 00:43:23,059
-Going to the sets.
-We were having a ball.

615
00:43:23,310 --> 00:43:27,731
It wasn't half bad for the girls
either, I have to say.

616
00:43:30,233 --> 00:43:31,985
It might have even worked.

617
00:43:32,235 --> 00:43:35,906
Yeah? Let's do that shit again.
Hey, hey. Stop.

618
00:43:37,908 --> 00:43:42,412
Shooting a Reebok ad down there.
Where are my endorsements?

619
00:43:42,829 --> 00:43:46,374
-Oh, Jay Mohr, "I love you."
-"I love you."

620
00:43:47,250 --> 00:43:50,796
I didn't get no love from
that Energizer Bunny or Nike.

621
00:43:51,046 --> 00:43:53,757
Obviously, I didn't get
love from Reebok.

622
00:43:54,007 --> 00:43:58,345
-Did I tell you my Reebok story?
- I gotta get back to Cush.

623
00:43:58,595 --> 00:44:03,850
Oh, your golden paycheque.
But wait, I'll boil it down for you.

624
00:44:04,059 --> 00:44:05,769
Fuck Reebok!

625
00:44:06,019 --> 00:44:08,855
All they do is ignore me.
Always have.

626
00:44:09,105 --> 00:44:10,941
Always have.

627
00:44:11,358 --> 00:44:16,154
You know what was great down there?
You unloaded that large chip...

628
00:44:16,363 --> 00:44:18,031
...on your shoulder.

629
00:44:18,281 --> 00:44:20,742
And you let people in.

630
00:44:22,327 --> 00:44:24,246
You were brilliant.

631
00:44:25,330 --> 00:44:26,748
-Brilliant?
-Brilliant.

632
00:44:26,957 --> 00:44:30,460
-Really?
-Take care, I'll see you tomorrow.

633
00:44:30,752 --> 00:44:34,589
-You love me now?
-I'm about showing you the money!

634
00:44:34,840 --> 00:44:38,802
I was just testing you,
but to hear you say that...

635
00:44:39,052 --> 00:44:42,389
...makes me love you, baby.
You know?

636
00:44:43,640 --> 00:44:46,309
-"You know?"
-"You know?"

637
00:44:47,018 --> 00:44:49,062
Pants were too long.

638
00:44:50,397 --> 00:44:52,357
-What size are you?
-12 and a half.

639
00:44:52,524 --> 00:44:56,152
Grab a couple pairs
of them new shoes by the door.

640
00:44:56,653 --> 00:44:58,238
That's Light field Lewis.

641
00:44:58,655 --> 00:45:03,994
I grew up with him. Didn't know he was
in the movie until after I saw it.

642
00:45:04,160 --> 00:45:06,746
-You're kidding me.
-Didn't know.

643
00:45:08,748 --> 00:45:10,000
This is great.

644
00:45:13,879 --> 00:45:17,424
Jimmy O'Connell, playing Nirvana
on the guitar.

645
00:45:19,843 --> 00:45:24,180
We lived in Seattle when rock
and sports started to be together.

646
00:45:24,347 --> 00:45:28,351
They'd have a highlight reel
of a game cut to Nirvana.

647
00:45:28,685 --> 00:45:33,690
I thought, "Something's happening.
These two never used to collide."

648
00:45:33,857 --> 00:45:37,444
So that's why he's singing
"Something In The Way."

649
00:45:38,153 --> 00:45:43,450
-This was just heartbreaking.
-Tom taking you on the big ride.

650
00:45:43,783 --> 00:45:46,453
-This scene was--
-Great piece of writing.

651
00:45:46,786 --> 00:45:49,915
It always got me. Now you know--

652
00:45:50,123 --> 00:45:53,335
On a page until it comes to life
like this.

653
00:45:53,710 --> 00:45:55,295
-Yeah, right.
-It's true.

654
00:45:55,462 --> 00:45:58,006
And the camera's creeping in.

655
00:45:58,298 --> 00:46:00,967
-New York City behind him.
-Oh, God.

656
00:46:01,134 --> 00:46:03,803
The lights. Success is fleeting.

657
00:46:03,970 --> 00:46:05,805
Look at his face.

658
00:46:06,139 --> 00:46:09,726
This is life draining from a man.

659
00:46:09,893 --> 00:46:11,269
Look at that!

660
00:46:19,569 --> 00:46:21,112
No comment.

661
00:46:28,078 --> 00:46:30,914
-He's got it wrong.
-You're on TV again.

662
00:46:31,164 --> 00:46:33,875
I'm sick of me, already.

663
00:46:34,084 --> 00:46:36,127
TEAM
CUSHMAN

664
00:46:36,336 --> 00:46:38,713
He puts the hat on.

665
00:46:38,880 --> 00:46:42,342
I'm gonna let you do it the hard way.

666
00:46:42,676 --> 00:46:45,637
Let's go,
you're gonna have to go hard.

667
00:46:45,804 --> 00:46:50,517
Before I go back to Denver,
we should put something on paper.

668
00:46:50,767 --> 00:46:53,311
Something that says you're with me.

669
00:46:53,561 --> 00:46:55,981
Not right now, Jerry.

670
00:46:56,815 --> 00:46:57,983
Oh, that.

671
00:47:02,195 --> 00:47:05,907
Do I know everything
there is to know here, Matt?

672
00:47:09,327 --> 00:47:12,580
You're not talking
with Bob Sugar, are you?

673
00:47:13,206 --> 00:47:16,960
Apparently, Denver would only
deal with him.

674
00:47:17,794 --> 00:47:20,672
Said who? Sugar?

675
00:47:21,631 --> 00:47:23,091
I'm learning as I go.

676
00:47:23,675 --> 00:47:28,847
So you empowered him
to deal with Denver behind my back?

677
00:47:29,139 --> 00:47:31,182
I'm sorry...

678
00:47:32,934 --> 00:47:36,021
-I love my son.
- I love your son!

679
00:47:36,730 --> 00:47:41,276
I brought Denver to 20 million.
They always deal with me.

680
00:47:41,526 --> 00:47:45,697
You listened to Sugar.
Bob Sugar, Matt, is a child.

681
00:47:45,947 --> 00:47:49,617
You let that snake in the door?

682
00:47:52,328 --> 00:47:57,709
Listen, rookie mistake.
I'll fix this Denver thing for you.

683
00:47:57,959 --> 00:48:01,004
You didn't sign anything
with Sugar, right?

684
00:48:03,381 --> 00:48:07,844
Matt? Tell me you didn't sign.

685
00:48:08,887 --> 00:48:11,598
Because I'm still sort of
moved by your...

686
00:48:11,848 --> 00:48:15,769
...my word is stronger
than oak" thing.

687
00:48:16,770 --> 00:48:20,148
-This is a little creepy.
-I know, it's "owie."

688
00:48:21,191 --> 00:48:24,986
You were in the lobby
with the black fella.

689
00:48:25,153 --> 00:48:27,030
Watch your mouth now.

690
00:48:27,989 --> 00:48:31,618
Sorry, Jerry.
I just want to play football.

691
00:48:34,871 --> 00:48:37,082
Never seen you look like that.

692
00:48:37,290 --> 00:48:40,210
I've never seen him like that.
Never.

693
00:48:40,877 --> 00:48:45,715
-Never seen you look like that.
-Kelly was great in this scene too.

694
00:48:49,427 --> 00:48:51,429
Everything's on the run.

695
00:48:51,679 --> 00:48:55,225
You and I are sales people.
We sell.

696
00:48:55,433 --> 00:48:59,229
It's not "Love me"
or "Trust my handshake"...

697
00:48:59,521 --> 00:49:02,565
...it's "Make the sale!
Get it signed.”

698
00:49:02,774 --> 00:49:05,443
Jump right into my nightmare.

699
00:49:05,652 --> 00:49:08,071
So now I can't be honest?

700
00:49:08,279 --> 00:49:13,326
-I'd prefer loyalty.
-What'd we say when we got together?

701
00:49:13,535 --> 00:49:15,453
Brutal truth. Remember?

702
00:49:16,329 --> 00:49:18,832
I think you added the "brutal.”

703
00:49:19,082 --> 00:49:24,462
There's a sensitivity thing that some
people have. I don't have it.

704
00:49:24,712 --> 00:49:27,841
I don't cry at movies,
or gush over babies...

705
00:49:28,091 --> 00:49:30,051
...don't do Christmas early...

706
00:49:30,301 --> 00:49:33,930
...and I don't tell a man who
screwed up our lives:

707
00:49:37,058 --> 00:49:41,354
She was training with Boom Boom
Mancini, am I right about that?

708
00:49:41,688 --> 00:49:44,649
Kelly was preparing for this moment.

709
00:49:46,693 --> 00:49:49,154
This wasn't just show up...

710
